The paper deals with the problem of parallel query processing on a large database, which is a core topic in the field of database systems (cs.DB). The study of algorithms with one round of communication and the complexity of communication suggests a focus on distributed systems (cs.DS) and parallel computing (cs.DC). The use of statistics and packings in the analysis of communication complexity points towards computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the mention of prior results on the MapReduce model suggests a possible connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
